Yes, it is true that all of the &quot;good&quot; Maia aided in the Great Battle, where the host of Valinor destroyed Thangorodrim and exiled Meklor, but they went back with the rest of the host afterwards (as did most of the Elves).  The Istari appeared about 1000 years into the 3rd age, landing at the Grey Havens.  They were sent to &quot;contest the power of Sauron, and to unite all those who had the will to resist him; but were forbidden to match his power with power, or to seek to dominate elves and men by force and fear&quot; (III, Apdx B).  It is obvious, in the first book (and movie) that Sauruman has broken this prohibition... but I won't spoil what happens next...<br>
